Mapping from BioticData to StoxBiotic data for different input file formats

Source: R/data.R
StoxBioticMapping.Rd

The StoxBioticFormat contains a fixed mapping between variables from the different input biotic data formats to the variables of the StoxBioticData. For variables that are not supported by StoxBiotic the function AddToStoxBiotic can be used to add these to the StoxBioticData. The function RedefineStoxBiotic can also be used to redefine variables in a StoxBioticData object. Both of these functions add data to the StoxBioticData object using the described in the Details.

Details

The mapping from the different biotic data format to StoxBiotic is different for different levels Some levels are directly mapped to a levels in StoxBioticData, whereas other levels are split into two levels of the StoxBioticData.
